{
  "texts": [
    "This conceptualization builds directly upon the exploration processes (March 1991; Benner and Tushman 2003).",
    "Such innovation typically demands substantial human input to define the problem space, conceptualize potential solutions, and implement novel approaches that do not have precedence within the project context.",
    "In software development contexts, capability innovation manifests as implementing new features that extend the project's capabilities.",
    "The second, iterative innovation aims at improving the quality of existing elements, refining them to function better and more reliably.",
    "Given that the main cognitive capacity for this task center on comprehension of the current context before making changes, this type draws on exploitation activities (March 1991; Benner and Tushman 2003) This innovation type requires understanding already implemented solutions and enhancing them in the current iteration (Medappa and Srivastava 2019)."
  ]
}